        <p class="homepage-link">
          <a href="/government/organisations/department-for-digital-culture-media-sport">Department for Digital, Culture, Media & Sport homepage</a>
</p>        <h1 class="main">Research at DCMS</h1>
        <p class="description">
          Details of the research done by and for DCMS and our sponsored bodies. 
        </p>
        <div class="body">
          <div class="govspeak">
<p>Evidence helps us see what is really happening in our sectors. It means we can assess and improve our work. To provide this evidence we collate statistical data and commission specific studies. Our sponsored bodies also publish their own research reports.</p>

<p>More information is available about our research in the following areas:</p>

<h2 id="taking-part">Taking Part</h2>
<p>The <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/taking-part">‘Taking Part’ survey</a> is a national survey of culture, leisure and sport.</p>

<h2 id="case">CASE</h2>
<p>The <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/case-programme">CASE programme</a>,  a joint research programme to strengthen our understanding of how best to deliver culture and sporting opportunities of the highest quality to the widest audience generating the best outcomes for society.</p>

<h2 id="research-studies">Research studies</h2>
<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-culture-media-sport/series/research">Research studies</a> exploring in depth the issues that face our sectors and ways we can address them.</p>

<h2 id="statistics">Statistics</h2>
<p>Authoritative <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-culture-media-sport/about/statistics">statistics</a> on all kinds of subjects related to our sectors.</p>

<h2 id="guidance-and-methods">Guidance and methods</h2>
<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/research-and-statistics-guidance">Guidance</a> on how we gather our information and the standards to which we adhere.</p>

<h2 id="research-links">Research links</h2>

<p>Many of our public bodies have research teams which commission and publish work on their sectors. Links to their research pages are listed below:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a rel="external" href="http://www.artscouncil.org.uk/what-we-do/research-and-data/">Arts Council</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="http://www.bfi.org.uk/education-research/film-industry-statistics-research">BFI</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="http://www.biglotteryfund.org.uk/research">Big Lottery Fund</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="http://www.gamblingcommission.gov.uk/research__consultations/research.aspx">Gambling Commission</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="http://www.geffrye-museum.org.uk/collections/research/">Geffrye Museum</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="http://www.hlf.org.uk/aboutus/howwework/Pages/Evaluation.aspx">Heritage Lottery Fund</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="https://historicengland.org.uk/research/">Historic England</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="https://ico.org.uk/about-the-ico/our-information/research-and-reports/">Information Commissioner’s Office</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="http://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/archives-sector/case-studies-and-research-reports/">National Archives</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="http://www.natlotcomm.gov.uk/publications-and-research.html">National Lottery Commission</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="https://www.royalparks.org.uk/park-management/visitor-research">Royal Parks</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="http://www.sportengland.org/research.aspx">Sport England</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="http://www.uksport.gov.uk/our-work/international-relations/research">UK Sport</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="http://www.visitbritain.org/insightsandstatistics/index.aspx">VisitBritain</a></li>
  <li><a rel="external" href="https://www.visitbritain.org/england-research-insights">VisitEngland</a></li>
</ul>

<p>The <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/longitudinal-data-library">DCMS Longitudinal Library</a> documents all longitudinal surveys containing questions relevant to the DCMS sectors (culture, media and sport).</p>

<p>Below is a list of other sites which contain useful research and statistical information on DCMS sectors.</p>

